    "where, y m represents the corresponding point of any point x i ∈ X in the source point cloud in the target point cloud.",
    "Equation (1) allows R and t to be solved by singular value decomposition (SVD).",
    "However, the corresponding point y m is usually unknown, so before solving the transformation, the corresponding relationship between the starting point pairs needs to be established:",
    "From the relationship between Equations (1), (2), we can see that the solution of Equation (2) depends on the known R and t, which is precisely the solution objective of Equation (1).",
    "Therefore, the conventional approaches such as ICP assumes initial R = I and t = 0."
